Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.82,0:00:05.78,Episode Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(724.091,814.091)\fade(255,0,255,0,1340,3700,4940)}Heroes over Wine
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.20,0:00:11.60,Thinking,,0,0,0,,On the third year of the Jian'an era (198 AD),
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.34,0:00:17.34,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Cao Cao, with the help of Liu Bei, conquered Xuzhou and Xiapi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.34,0:00:24.28,Thinking,,0,0,0,,He strangled Lü Bu at White Gate Tower and accepted Zhang Liao's surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.39,0:00:28.79,Thinking,,0,0,0,,He thus removed a cause for great trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.94,0:00:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ministers who have rendered merits shall be rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.18,0:00:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,With the nation maintained through your efforts, We can be at rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.46,0:00:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you with achievements shall \Nrequest Sire Cao for your rewards.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.14,0:00:49.66,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(210.682,717.955)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,2220,2500)}Cao Cao\NStyled: Mengde
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.94,0:00:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,As you command, Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.02,0:00:55.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Beloved liege-man, you memorialized yesterday about Liu Bei's exploits.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.65,0:00:57.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Why not call him to an audience with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.39,0:01:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As you command.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.23,0:01:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Bei is called for an audience with His Majesty!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.90,0:01:12.96,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(308.864,689.318)}Liú Bèi, \Nstyled Xuándé
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.04,0:01:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My humblest respects, Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.65,0:01:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live! Long, long live!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.90,0:01:28.90,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1188.409,711.818)}Emperor Xian of Hàn
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.92,0:01:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You may rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.12,0:01:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.86,0:01:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You do look majestic. Who are your ancestors?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.92,0:01:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Your subject is a descendant of {\i1}Prince Jing of Zhongshan,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.92,0:01:42.76,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: Liu Sheng, Prince of Zhongshan, born ? - 113 BC
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.84,0:01:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and a distant descendant of {\i1}Emperor Jing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.94,0:01:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the grandson of Liu Xiong and the son of Liu Hong.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.60,0:01:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly. Let us check the imperial clan's record.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.26,0:01:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.81,0:01:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.72,0:01:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Read it out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.68,0:02:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.39,0:02:09.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Emperor Jing had fourteen sons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.39,0:02:09.88,Note (Potential style?),NTP,0,0,0,,Note: Emperor Jing of Hàn, born 188 BC – 9 March 141 BC
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.24,0:02:13.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,The seventh was Prince Jing \Nof Zhongshan, Liu Sheng.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.25,0:02:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sheng beget the Marquis of Lucheng, Liu Ang.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.10,0:02:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ang beget the Marquis of Zhang, Liu Lu.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.30,0:02:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Lu beget the Marquis of Yishui, Liu Lian.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.34,0:02:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Lian beget the Marquis of Qinyang, Liu Ying.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.24,0:02:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Ying beget the Marquis of Anguo, Liu Jian.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.72,0:02:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Jian beget the Marquis of Guangling, Liu Ai.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.20,0:02:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ai beget the Marquis of Jiaoshui, Liu Xian.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.82,0:02:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Xian beget the Marquis of Zuyi, Liu Shu.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.42,0:02:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Shu beget the Marquis of Qiyang, Liu Yi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.76,0:02:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yi beget the Marquis of Yuanze, Liu Bi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.10,0:02:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Bi beget the Marquis of Yingchuan, Liu Da.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.34,0:02:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Da beget the Marquis of Banling, Liu Buyi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.60,0:02:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Buyi beget the Marquis of Jichuan, Liu Hui.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.10,0:02:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hui beget the Prefect of Fan, \Nof Dōng-commandery, Liu Xiong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.10,0:02:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Xiong beget Liu Hóng, who held no rank.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.88,0:02:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Bei is Liu Hóng's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.59,0:03:18.39,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Cáo Cāo has amassed power. \NNot one matter of the state is of my doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.19,0:03:22.90,Thinking,,0,0,0,,Now that I have found this hero, \NI will finally have salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.62,0:03:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, rise, Imperial Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.59,0:03:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Your Majesty!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.42,0:03:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow Us to the main hall to pay our respects, as {\i1}Our relative.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.40,0:04:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Court is dismissed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.10,0:04:27.22,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1247.727,703.636)\fade(255,0,255,0,340,1860,2100)}Xún Yōu \NStyled: Gōng Dá
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.56,0:04:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.58,0:04:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the Emperor acknowledged \NLiu Bei as the Imperial Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.46,0:04:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This may be problematic to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.93,0:04:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Though Liu Bei acts as the Imperial Uncle,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.07,0:04:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the one issuing the decrees in the Emperor's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.94,0:04:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How could he not obey them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.22,0:04:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, if I keep Liu Bei here in Xǔdū (Xǔchāng),
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.45,0:04:50.25,Default,,0,0,0,,his bond with the Emperor all the more has him deeper in my grasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.19,0:04:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Why fear him?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.69,0:05:00.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Chancellor, your might and prestige increases every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.68,0:05:03.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Why not conduct yourself like a king?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Before that, let us raise a toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.60,0:05:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The imperial family currently has many supporters and must not be underestimated.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.33,0:05:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I already asked for the Emperor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.04,0:05:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to go hunting tommorow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.10,0:05:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We shall see how they act.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.61,0:05:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor! Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.01,0:05:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, on your orders,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.82,0:05:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I have prepared a house in the vicinity of your mansion for Liu Bei.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.42,0:06:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Send people to keep an eye on Liu Bei at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.08,0:06:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Report back when possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.68,0:06:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.32,0:06:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Brothers, you cannot make too much noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is our courtyard. What's it to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.10,0:06:39.02,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(184.091,709.773)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,2580,2900)}Zhāng Fēi\NStyled: Yìdé
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.64,0:06:38.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Brother, why are you neglecting your duties?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.74,0:06:40.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,You're just growing vegetables everyday!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.24,0:06:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The Emperor has acknowledged me as his uncle,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.58,0:06:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so everyone is keeping an eye on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.12,0:06:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We must be very cautious in our manners and our words.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.94,0:06:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so that others will not see us as impudent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.58,0:07:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, we live next to the Chancellor, so all the more to be vigilant.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.88,0:07:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just too paranoid!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.06,0:07:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't caused any trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.86,0:07:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do they care about\N what we do or say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.34,0:07:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Third Brother, he hasn't spoken very clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.18,0:07:24.62,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(208.636,695.455)\fade(255,0,255,0,350,2100,2420)}Guān Yǔ\NStyled: Yúncháng
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.32,0:07:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to be careful, otherwise {\i1}he{\i0} might get in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.46,0:08:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(728.194,918.409)}The realm is not at ease. \NIs hunting really appropriate?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.44,0:08:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(697.467,912.273)}Your Majesty is mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.44,0:08:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(711.806,918.409)}Sovereigns of old toured during autumn and hunted during winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.00,0:08:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(711.806,918.409)}To leave the palace every season\Nwould show your magnanimity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.36,0:08:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(705.661,910.227)}Whatever the turmoil,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.88,0:08:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(717.952,912.273)}Your Majesty would still display your authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.36,0:08:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(717.952,916.364)}What problem is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.84,0:09:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty. Please?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.08,0:09:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Go call the Imperial Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.59,0:09:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The Imperial Uncle is called!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.44,0:09:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I offer my respects, Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.28,0:09:55.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We wish to see you hunt, Imperial Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.76,0:09:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As you command.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.58,0:10:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice! Nice! Good shot, Imperial Uncle!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.82,0:10:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty, you praise me too highly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.89,0:10:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let His Majesty hunt!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.94,0:11:14.30,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1241.591,744.545)}Dǒng Chéng
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.83,0:11:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you try it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.88,0:12:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chancellor has hit his target! He has hit his target!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.09,0:12:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Chancellor has hit his target! He has hit his target!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.12,0:12:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The Emperor has hit his target! \NHe has hit his target!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.93,0:12:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Emperor's golden arrow! \NHe's hit his target!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.24,0:13:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Emperor's golden arrow! \NHe's hit his target!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.54,0:13:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Long live the Emperor!\N May he live 10,000 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.62,0:13:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, such a divine shot is seldom in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.56,0:13:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a blessing from the Emperor!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.35,0:13:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A blessing from the Emperor. \NHad I lacked the Emperor's bow,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.90,0:13:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,how could I have made such a shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.88,0:14:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.96,0:14:52.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Brother, that bastard Cao Cao humiliated his Majesty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.92,0:14:55.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I would have rid the land of a villain had I killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.83,0:15:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you stop me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.34,0:15:14.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Cao Cao and the Emperor were only a few inches apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.04,0:15:17.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,and his aides were all around him too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.16,0:15:21.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Second Brother, if you acted recklessly in a fit of rage,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.20,0:15:23.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,the Emperor would've been harmed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.12,0:15:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The fault would have been ours. You have to let a rat go lest you smash the dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.66,0:15:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't kill this bastard today, \Nthere will be grave consequences!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.81,0:15:53.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,All of the ministers received the nation's grace,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.20,0:15:57.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,yet in this crisis, not one comes to our aid!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.08,0:15:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.02,0:16:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.66,0:16:04.70,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(247.5,681.136)\fade(255,0,255,0,400,1780,2100)}Fu Wan
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.72,0:16:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The General of the Chariots and the State Uncle, {\i1}Dǒng Chéng
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.74,0:16:09.86,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: State Uncle（国舅）is either the maternal uncle of the Emperor, or Emperor's brother-in-law
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.08,0:16:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Summon him now. We have urgent matters to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.35,0:16:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't act recklessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.62,0:16:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If such is the case, what do you suggest we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.11,0:16:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.54,0:16:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(717.952,918.409)}Your Majesty, use your brocade robe and jade belt,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.68,0:16:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,920.455)}and hide an edict in them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.95,0:16:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,920.455)}Later, summon Dǒng Chéng,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.58,0:16:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(711.806,918.409)}gift him these clothes and send him back to read the edict, to show intention to rid of traitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.66,0:16:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(711.806,914.318)}Not even the gods or spirits will know of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.86,0:17:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(695.42,912.273)}Worthy subject, wear this robe
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.52,0:17:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(664.695,916.364)}and fasten this jade belt,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.64,0:17:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,891.818)}so that you feel you're always by Our side!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.10,0:17:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Majesty!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.48,0:17:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Our liege-man, when you go back, examine it very carefully. Don't reject Our good will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.39,0:17:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Here comes the Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.54,0:18:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How is Liu Bei doing these days?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.12,0:18:17.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I asked his servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.20,0:18:20.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,They say he reads in his chamber\Nor is sipping tea in the veranda.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.94,0:18:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,After returning from the imperial hunt, he started growing vegetables.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.72,0:18:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He tends the orchard every day without rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.60,0:18:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? He grows vegetables?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.24,0:18:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,He seems to be quite idle. \NAre you sure he isn't just avoiding me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.54,0:18:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,State Uncle, why are you hiding from me also?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.80,0:18:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.80,0:19:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, you came to the palace quite early. What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.40,0:19:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,His Majesty has summoned me to give me a brocade robe and a belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.07,0:19:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Today of all days? Why has he has given you a present?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.68,0:19:22.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,His Majesty recalled when I rescued him in the Western Capital (Cháng'ān).
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.08,0:19:25.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,He summoned me to talk about the past and gave me this present.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.74,0:19:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hand over the belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.75,0:19:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Seize it from him!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.44,0:20:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is an exquisite jade belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.46,0:20:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How does it look on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.16,0:20:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It fits you perfectly, Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.10,0:20:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, how about you give me the robe and belt as a present, State Uncle?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.34,0:20:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I dare not give away the sovereign's gifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.64,0:20:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you like it, Chancellor, I can present another robe for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.02,0:21:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,State Uncle, could those robes hide plots in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.47,0:21:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, if you insist, you may have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.18,0:21:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the accusation of a hidden plot?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.34,0:21:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,State Uncle, how could I keep a gift from the Emperor?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.23,0:21:45.79,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Our liege-man, when you go back, examine it very carefully. Don't reject Our good will.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.80,0:23:20.16,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(717.952,916.364)}"It is said amongst people's relations, \Nthat of a father and his son comes first."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.16,0:23:24.16,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(722.047,918.409)}"Amongst social ties, that of a sovereign and his minister is the strongest."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.16,0:23:27.08,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(711.806,924.545)}"The rebel Cao Cao abuses power for his enjoyment."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.15,0:23:30.76,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(715.903,908.182)}"He oppresses the family and, with the support of his armies,"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.76,0:23:32.64,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(703.614,914.318)}"undermining the imperium."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.12,0:23:37.12,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(717.952,918.409)}"Policies, rewards and punishments no longer depend on Us."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.12,0:23:43.72,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(693.372,904.091)}"At all times, We have troubled thoughts, that the world may be at the brink of peril."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.90,0:23:49.74,Thinking,,0,0,0,,{\pos(705.661,924.545)}"You are a grand minister of \Nthe nation and a dear relative of Ours."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.25,0:23:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(705.661,916.364)}"Remember the struggle met by our First Emperor."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.88,0:23:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(717.952,920.455)}"Gather both loyal and righteous heroes to eliminate the villains within court."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.36,0:24:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,922.5)}"To pacify the state, honour the spirit of the nation."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.48,0:24:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(736.386,910.227)}"We entrust you this edict, written with the blood of Our finger."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.12,0:24:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(722.047,922.5)}"Consider this carefully, do not let down Our wishes."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.26,0:24:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The impudence!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.23,0:24:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Zǐfú.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.59,0:24:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If Lord Cao is in danger, \NI must inform him immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.74,0:24:39.98,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(222.955,490.909)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,1850,2220)}Wáng Zǐfú
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.20,0:24:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Zifu, if that's what you want, my life is worth little compared to the fate of the Hàn dynasty!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.72,0:25:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Dǒng, I would not be where I am without the Hàn Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.92,0:25:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I lack a loyal heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.14,0:25:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I am willing to lend you a hand in purging the traitors to the state!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.98,0:25:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you come to visit me so late, Imperial Uncle, you must have a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.55,0:25:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,To come in plain daylight would make Cao Cao suspicious, so I've come late at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.82,0:25:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Fetch wine for our guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.64,0:25:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.66,0:25:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday, Yunchang wanted to kill Cao Cao in the hunting grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.80,0:25:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You signaled him to stop and shook your head. Why is that, General?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.47,0:25:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you realize, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.08,0:25:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody else knows it. Only I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.25,0:26:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother saw Cao Cao humiliate our sovereign and he was enraged.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.46,0:26:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,State Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.90,0:26:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If all ministers were like you, Yunchang, who would worry about peace in the Empire?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.20,0:26:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How is Chancellor Cao's regime not peaceful?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.86,0:26:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,State Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.20,0:26:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, you are the Imperial Uncle of the Hàn dynasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.92,0:26:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Your words are usually so honest. Why are you lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.10,0:26:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,State Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.70,0:26:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I feared you were lying, so I was just testing you, nothing more.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.91,0:26:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.28,0:26:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.17,0:27:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.97,0:27:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Third Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.44,0:27:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,This...  Our glorious Hàn Empire...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.35,0:27:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,To think that our Emperor, who stands above all...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.45,0:27:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,has to... has to... has to resort to {\i1}a blood edict{\i0} to his ministers!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.04,0:28:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.78,0:28:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.88,0:28:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,General!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.52,0:28:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,General of the Chariots; {\i1}Dǒng Chéng{\i0},\N Deputy Minister of Works;{\i1} Wang Zifu,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.00,0:28:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Cavalry Colonel; {\i1}Zhǒng Jí{\i0}, \NFaithful Gentleman; {\i1}Wú Shuò,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.06,0:28:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,General of Clear Loyalty; {\i1}Wú Zǐlán {\i0}and the Administrator of Xīliáng; {\i1}Mǎ Téng.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.12,0:28:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I have received an imperial order to expel the rebels, I will do my utmost!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.84,0:28:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Brother. Bring me a brush.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.14,0:28:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.30,0:29:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Orders from the Chancellor.\N You must go immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.33,0:29:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.84,0:29:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. He only told me to call you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.06,0:29:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me pull the bucket from the well first.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.22,0:30:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord Liu has arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.62,0:30:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been doing really great work at your house!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.95,0:30:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to be pretty carefree growing your orchard, Xuande. It must be hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.16,0:30:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Such things are irrelevant. Chancellor, why have you summoned me?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.82,0:31:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuande, I just saw the plums on the trees were green and felt some nostalgia.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.14,0:31:09.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,When I was campaigning against Zhang Xiu,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.72,0:31:13.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,there was no water on the way \Nand the troops were extremely thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.03,0:31:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought of something brilliant. I pointed ahead and said that there was a plum forest there.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.04,0:31:26.20,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: This is the origin of the Chinese idiom "望梅止渴", from {\i1}A New Account of the Tales of the World.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.08,0:31:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as they heard that, their mouths started watering and they were no longer thirsty.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.46,0:31:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing a plum tree today, I can't help but to behold it in admiration.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.42,0:31:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It also happens that it is ripe. Let us have a toast with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.36,0:31:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor. Look. There's a dragon hanging on the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.22,0:31:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(713.855,924.545)}The dragon hanging from the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.52,0:32:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(697.467,916.364)}looks like he's curling about,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.80,0:32:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,938.864)}as if to turn seas and rivers over.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.86,0:32:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A truly admirable sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.12,0:32:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sire, do you understand the many forms of dragons?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.88,0:32:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I do not know. Please, explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.90,0:32:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(717.952,902.045)}Dragons can be large or small, they can soar or hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.98,0:32:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(713.855,902.045)}The large ones births clouds and breathes mist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.84,0:32:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(715.903,902.045)}The small ones conceal themselves from sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.76,0:32:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(699.517,902.045)}Those that fly soar across creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.97,0:32:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}those that hide dwell within the great waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.84,0:32:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(722.047,902.045)}Here, deep within spring, is when dragons form,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.02,0:32:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(715.903,902.045)}like men with the will to conquer Four Seas.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.52,0:32:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,902.045)}The large ones births clouds and breathes mist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.62,0:33:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(722.047,902.045)}The small ones conceal themselves from sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.35,0:33:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(707.709,902.045)}Those that fly soar across creation,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.96,0:33:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(711.806,902.045)}Those that hide dwell within the great waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.08,0:33:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720,902.045)}Among all creatures, the dragon can be compared to the heroes in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.68,0:33:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(715.903,902.045)}Xuande, since you have ventured across the land, I assume you know such heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.76,0:33:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(713.855,902.045)}I ask thee to inform me who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.18,0:33:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}How could I recognize these heroes with just my eyes?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.02,0:33:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Don't be so modest!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.20,0:33:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Thanks to your favor, I have a post as an official.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.70,0:33:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}As for the heroes of the world, I regretfully do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.96,0:33:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Perhaps you don't remember their faces, but you must heard of their reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.24,0:34:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Is Yuán Shù of Huáinán,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.64,0:34:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}with his abundant lands \Nand troops, count as a hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.90,0:34:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Nothing but dried bones in a grave! His defeat is inevitable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.98,0:34:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Yuán Shào of Héběi! His clan with \Nfour generations of Excellencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.26,0:34:23.56,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: The Excellencies are the highest \Nofficials in the Imperial Court
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.18,0:34:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}He waits in Jì Province like a crouching tiger,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.62,0:34:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}and has many capable men under his command. Is he a hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.34,0:34:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Yuan Shao appears fierce, but has no guts!\N He schemes, but lacks decisiveness!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.50,0:34:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Conservative, despite his ambitions. \NOnly sees minutiae over the big picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.74,0:34:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}He's not a hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.08,0:34:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}There's one renowned for his nobility,\Nwhose name echoes throughout the land—
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.64,0:34:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Is Liú Jǐngshēng a hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.52,0:34:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Liú Biǎo has nothing behind his reputation. \N A magpie, not a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.44,0:35:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}There's a man of valour who rules over Jiāngdōng.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.10,0:35:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Surely, Sūn Bófū is a hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.84,0:35:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Sūn Cè rides on his father's name! He's no hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.50,0:35:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}What of Liú Jìyù of Yì Province, is he a hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.32,0:35:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Liú Zhāng may be of the imperial family, but he's nothing more than a watchdog.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.80,0:35:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}How can he be a hero?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.90,0:35:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}What about Zhāng Xiù, \NZhāng Lǔ, Hán Suì and the rest?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.08,0:35:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}All these lesser men, \Nare they really worth mentioning?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.00,0:35:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Other than these, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.18,0:36:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Heroes harbor grand ideals in their hearts and have methods to fulfill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.92,0:36:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Schemes within schemes all-embracing,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.52,0:36:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}and the will to bring all to their mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.44,0:36:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Who can be considered one?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.82,0:36:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Right now, the heroes of these lands,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.52,0:36:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}are only {\i1}you{\i0}, sire, and {\i1}I!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.88,0:37:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}Such tremendous ferocity! That was really close.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.06,0:37:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}How can a grown man be afraid of thunder?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.28,0:37:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}The Sage One said that one must change his countenance before the sudden thunder.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.60,0:37:25.60,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note: "The Sage One" refers to Confucius.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.66,0:37:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(709.758,902.045)}How can I not be afraid?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.32,0:37:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If we stay in Xǔdū, Cao Cao will harm us sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.65,0:37:51.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,It is said that Yuan Shu has rebelled in Huáinán.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.64,0:37:55.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,He wants to forfeit the imperial seal\N and his title to Yuan Shao.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.50,0:37:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If Yuan Shu is going to surrender to Shao, he must go through Xu Province.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.32,0:38:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We must seize this chance and ask to halt Yuan Shu,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.24,0:38:06.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,claiming to block the two Yuan's merge,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.32,0:38:09.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,but really for us to gain independence.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.20,0:38:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.28,0:38:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If we ask for troops \Nto block off Yuan Shu,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.55,0:38:18.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,this too will be ridding\N Cao Cao of a great threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.32,0:38:20.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,He will have no reason to decline.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.16,0:38:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. I will memorialize to the throne immediately, asking for troops and march off.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.86,0:38:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.86,0:38:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.78,0:38:35.98,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(193.57,681.136)\fade(255,0,255,0,340,1820,2180)}Guō Jiā\NStyled: Fèngxiào
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.22,0:38:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, I know you must have \Na greater reason for not killing Liu Bei.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.96,0:38:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you must not let him go either.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.50,0:38:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,As ancients say: Letting an enemy go will bring trouble for generations!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.22,0:38:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you reconsider!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.32,0:38:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I've already sent {\i1}Zhū Líng{\i0} \Nand {\i1}Lù Zhāo {\i0}to accompany Liu Bei.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.84,0:38:53.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,They may leave as his deputy officers,\N but I have them to keep watch on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.76,0:38:55.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I know Liu Bei wouldn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.80,0:39:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Attendants.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.68,0:39:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.08,0:39:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Summon Xu Chu now.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.26,0:39:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.71,0:39:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,General, look. The men sent by the Chancellor have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.06,0:39:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What have you come for, General Xǔ Chǔ?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.86,0:39:36.78,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1187.026,664.773)\fade(255,0,255,0,420,1500,1900)}Xǔ Chǔ\NStyled: Zhòngkāng
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.04,0:39:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,By order of the Chancellor, you must go back, for there is a meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.72,0:39:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the general is on the field, he can't accept the sovereign's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.00,0:39:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I already took my leave before the Emperor with the Chancellor's permission. There's nothing to discuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.34,0:39:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You should leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.08,0:39:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If you insist, I will return to the Chancellor and pass your message.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.50,0:40:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Farewell!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.90,0:40:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Zhu Ling and Lu Zhao!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.36,0:40:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.67,0:40:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Order both the infantry and cavalry to march faster and maintain it!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.74,0:40:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, why are you in \Nsuch a hurry to campaign?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.05,0:40:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I am like a bird in a cage, or like a fish in a net.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.26,0:40:31.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If we hurry, we will be like a bird soaring through heaven, or a fish within the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.46,0:40:33.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,We will never be restrained again! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.40,0:40:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother!
